						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 969, Sarvajit, • • • • śu. 5, Ādityavāra.</hi> It refers itself to the reign of the Chālukya king <hi rend="bold">Traiḷōkyamalladēva,</hi> whose feudatory <hi rend="bold">Traiḷōkyamalla-Nanninoḷamba-Pallava-Permānaḍi</hi> is mentioned. <hi rend="bold">Udayāditya Ēcha-Nāyaka,</hi> under the orders of (Ghaṭṭidēva), is said to have gone on horse-back and catching hold of thieves who had stolen the cows of Kōgaḷi slew them and died after getting the cows back.</p>						

						</summary>
